{"id": "d5b4v0", "title": "\"General Motors strike not likely to be resolved anytime soon: experts\"", "selftext": "[NBC News article](https://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/general-motors-strike-not-likely-be-resolved-anytime-soon-experts-n1055086)\n\nApparently there is significant friction on both sides of the negotiating table against coming to an agreement: the UAW wants to show its rank and file members that it's not just [blowing their dues on vacations and booze](https://www.detroitnews.com/story/business/autos/2019/09/12/uaw-presidents-gary-jones-dennis-williams-implicated-in-federal-probe/2302410001/) and is actually \"fighting\" for a good deal, while GM Management doesn't want to be stuck paying out the ass for US labor if/when Tariff Daddy [spikes the price of parts from Mexico](https://www.cnbc.com/2019/05/31/trumps-mexico-tariff-threat-puts-gm-fiat-chrysler-in-a-bind.html?__source=twitter%7Cmain) or when they get caught in the middle of [his fight with California on regulatory fuel standards](https://www.cnbc.com/2019/08/22/trump-forces-ford-gm-to-walk-a-fine-line-on-fuel-economy-rules.html).\n\nDespite having [stocked up 77 days worth of new production vehicles](https://www.autonews.com/sales/automakers-inventory-high-uaw-walks-job), GM won't be able to deliver them because [the Teamsters are refusing to transport them](https://www.foxbusiness.com/industrials/teamsters-refusing-transport-gm-vehicles-solidarity-with-uaw) in solidarity with UAW. The longer a deal takes to make, the worse it is for GM. Their stock price is [down 4.25% today](https://www.google.com/search?rlz=1C1CHBF_enUS854US854&amp;sxsrf=ACYBGNRUYCCNP9DMUjWoVA7rQywRXDRM1Q:1568688626097&amp;q=NYSE:+GM&amp;stick=H4sIAAAAAAAAAONgecRoyi3w8sc9YSmdSWtOXmNU4-IKzsgvd80rySypFJLgYoOy-KR4uLj0c_UNjCoyTCryeBaxcvhFBrtaKbj7AgCNzFeVRQAAAA&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwijlMnC7NbkAhV5CTQIHYliBkwQsRUwKXoECA8QBw&amp;biw=1920&amp;bih=937).\n\nThe UAW has a $721MM strike fund, enough to pay reduced wages to members for over a year. From the article: ...\"both sides are bracing for a long and costly fight\". \u201cIt will go on as long as it\u2019s going to take to achieve our bargaining goals\".\n\nTL;DR: Bought GM 35 PUTs 18 OCT", "created_utc": 1568689497, "permalink": "/r/wallstreetbets/comments/d5b4v0/general_motors_strike_not_likely_to_be_resolved/", "is_self": true}